      <bioghist id="aspace_b3e0b31f0730dd74ee563f6041c4b2db">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Human Culture and Behavior was a Yale College Divisional Major that focused on the study of human behavior through the disciplines of anthropology, sociology, psychology, zoology and history.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_1e3d645f9b127f9c99c50155ee288d8a">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of files maintained by Rollin G. Osterweis documenting the Yale Divisional Major program. Included are printed materials, memoranda, statements and gradesheets of divisional major students, and hand-outs from the Yale Human Culture and Behavior program.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
